This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with sentence compression, which is a natural language processing task. Additionally, the paper mentions techniques such as integer linear programming (ILP) and optimization, which are commonly used in computational linguistics research. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a novel algorithm for sentence compression. 

The sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) is also a possibility as the paper may involve training a model to generate the k-best compressions. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as sentence compression can be seen as a way to improve the efficiency of information retrieval systems by reducing the size of the text to be searched. 

Finally, Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) is a less likely sub-category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for sentence compression, but it is not the main focus of the paper.
